From "O" to meh...
Sep 2024 • Couples
We've been going to Vegas forever and to the Bellagio for decades and it has been our favorite place to stay.

With that said, this recent visit has us looking elsewhere next time.

Stayed in the fountain view room with is awesome. The shower leaked onto the bathroom floor and had to pile towels against it for the 3 days we were in that room, engineering never fixed it. Switched to a downgraded room the last day.

Over 4 days of gambling for 4+ hours each day, we got drink server for maybe 6 drinks over 4 days. The smoke was worse here than any of the other casinos we visited during this trip.

Peterossian is a great place to have a morning cappuccino and listen to the piano or a late night bite and a drink to chill. Staff is great and Morgan the pianist is a gem.

The Le Cirque restaurant food is amazing. The service is stellar! Tom, Maurice, and the awesome Greek server were top notch.

Skip Prime, there are a million places in Vegas that have better steaks. Too many things wrong with this place to write here.

The Yellowtail restaurant is definitely worth visiting. Our suggestions: Akira Back Tuna Pizza, Edamame w/ sweet chili...

The pizza at the snack place is solid but is really busy late in the evening. Eric should be recognized for his leadership in a hectic situation and his management and troubleshooting skills.

Tito at the front desk is a true example of what hospitality means. A true asset to the Bellagio.

$24 for a bottle of Fiji water is criminal.
Written September 4, 2024
